fields.descriptive_line: Double sided print. On one side a print entitled 'Political Dreamings! - Visions of Peace! - Perspective Horrors!' published in London by Hannah Humphrey on 9th November 1801. On the other a print entitled 'The National Parachute, - or - John Bull conducted to Plenty and Emancipation' published in London by Hannah Humphrey on 10th July 1802, Harry Beard Collection.

fields.public_access_description: Double sided print. On one side a print entitled 'Political Dreamings! - Visions of Peace! - Perspective Horrors!' in which William Windham dreams of a French invasion of Britain with Napoleon Bonaparte leading Britannia to the guillotine. On the other side is a print depicitng the Prime Minister William Pitt and is entitled 'The National Parachute, - or - John Bull conducted to Plenty and Emancipation'. Both prints were published in London by Hannah Humphrey.
fields.credit: Harry R. Beard Collection, given by Isobel Beard
